<HEADLINE>
<P>
CUBAN FOLKLORIC GROUP AT PASADENA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cuba's oldest folkloric group, Los Munequitos de Matanzas, will perform Friday 
and Saturday at 8 p.m. at Pasadena City College. Founded in 1952, Los 
Munequitos de Matanzas is a 14-member percussion group, song and dance ensemble 
specializing in traditional rituals and rumbas. 
</P>
<P>
 A post-concert dance party will be held at 10:30 p.m. Friday at Steven's Steak 
House in the City of Commerce, featuring Afro-Cuban music by Mazacote and MC1. 
All proceeds from both events will benefit the Institute of Cuban Folkloric 
Studies. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets for the Pasadena performances are available from Ticketmaster and the 
Institute of Cuban Folkloric Studies. Prices are $15 pre-sale and $20 at the 
door. The post-concert dance party tickets are $15 and available only from the 
Institute of Folkloric Studies at (818) 453-8032. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Munequitos will also offer percussion and dance workshops on Saturday from 
noon to 2 p.m. at Pasadena College Studios and will perform on Sunday from 1 to 
3 p.m. at the African Market Place in Rancho Cienega Park, 5001 Rodeo Road. 
Workshop tickets are $24 pre-sale from the Institute of Cuban Folkloric Studies 
or $30 at the door. 
</P>
