<P>
 Ortho Mattress Co., two radio stations and the makers of the new comedy, "Camp 
Nowhere," are sponsoring a bed race down Ventura Boulevard in Woodland Hills on 
Saturday from 10 a.m. until noon. The vehicles, twin-sized beds on four wheels, 
will be supplied by the mattress company. The public is welcome. Is Ortho's 
participation an indication that the movie will put viewers to sleep? 
