COMMUNITY NEWS: WEST LOS ANGELES; BLAZES DAMAGE 3 BUILDINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATHIS CHAZANOV 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Pieces of burning charcoal set fire to the roof of an apartment house in West 
Los Angeles on Sunday night just eight minutes before a fire of unknown origin 
destroyed three units of another residential building nearby. 
</P>
<P>
 Fire officials said there was no apparent connection between the $3,000 
rooftop blaze at 10917 Rochester Ave.-- which broke out during a rooftop 
barbecue -- and the later, more serious fire at 11520 Wyoming Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 Two residents and a firefighter were treated and released for minor injuries 
suffered during the second fire, which caused an estimated $540,000 worth of 
damage.  
</P>
<P>
 Early Monday, yet another fire was reported in an empty four-car garage at 
1516 Westwood Blvd. Damage to that structure was estimated at $55,000. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators are looking into causes of the fires.MATHIS CHAZANOV 
</P>
