<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: BEVERLY HILLS; HOME BOMBING SUSPECT IN CRITICAL CONDITION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man who police believe set off an explosion that destroyed a vacant house 
last week remained in critical condition on Wednesday with second- and 
third-degree burns. 
</P>
<P>
 The explosion and resulting fire occurred Aug. 11 at 309 N. Foothill Road, 
just blocks from the headquarters of the Beverly Hills police and fire 
departments. 
</P>
<P>
 The man, in his mid-40s, allegedly doused the one-story residence with 
gasoline and then ignited it with a match, apparently while he was still inside 
the house, said Beverly Hills Police Lt. Joe Lombardi. The resulting explosion 
virtually blew the house off its foundation. 
</P>
<P>
 Lombardi said police had not determined a motive and knew of no connection 
between the man and the residence. 
</P>
