<P>
ROLLER HOCKEY; BLADES ROLL TO GAME 1 VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Craig Charron scored four goals and had three assists to lead the Blades to a 
14-6 victory over the San Diego Barracudas in Game 1 of a first-round Roller 
Hockey International playoff series before 1,974 Wednesday night at the San 
Diego Sports Arena. 
</P>
<P>
 Steve Bogoyevac had a goal and five assists for the Blades, whose 18-4 
regular-season record was the best in the Pacific Division. 
</P>
<P>
 Game 2 of the two-game series is Friday night at 7:30 at the Forum. If the 
Barracudas win, the teams will play a 12-minute game immediately afterward to 
determine the series winner. 
</P>
