<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEYWIDE FOCUS : STEVE ALLEN TO HOST ETHNIC CELEBRATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF SCHNAUFER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Entertainer Steve Allen will host the first Heritage Ball in September to 
promote ethnic pride among San Fernando Valley residents. 
</P>
<P>
 The event will be held 5:30 p.m. Sept. 25 at the Warner Center Marriott, 21850 
Oxnard St. in Woodland Hills.It will raise funds for the first Valley Heritage 
Fair in April. 
</P>
<P>
 Guests, who will pay $50 per person, are invited to attend in either black 
tie, the native dress of another country or the traditional clothing of their 
own native country. 
</P>
<P>
 "We're showing that we're Americans, but we are proud of our heritage," said 
Richard Hardman, president of Valley Heritage Fair Inc., the nonprofit 
organization holding the ball. 
</P>
<P>
 Allen, a popular television and film personality, will serve as master of 
ceremonies, Hardman said. Television weatherman Dr. George Fischbeck will be 
honorary chairman. 
</P>
<P>
 Valley Heritage Fair Inc. was founded in 1993 to showcase ethnic groups in the 
community. The fair, scheduled for April 22 and 23, will feature ethnic games, 
food and entertainment. JEFF SCHNAUFER 
</P>
</TEXT>
