<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: MONROVIA; POLICE, MERCHANTS TEAM IN BIKE SAFETY PROGRAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Monrovia Police officers will be on the lookout for kids wearing their bicycle 
helmets. Every child they find will receive a special ticket that will have 
words of thanks and encouragement from the issuing police officer.The effort is 
part of a bicycle safety program that started in June. 
</P>
<P>
 Project HELP, or The Helmet, Education and Law Program, was designed to 
promote good habits in young bicycle riders. The program encourages them to 
wear their bicycle helmets in accordance with a law that requires all riders 
under 18 to wear helmets by Jan. 1, 1995. 
</P>
<P>
 The program is supported by a dozen local businesses that offer awards for 
kids who visit their stores and present their ticket. Plans to expand the 
ongoing program will depend on its initial success. 
</P>
<P>
 The goal of Project HELP is to keep bicycle riders safe as well as build 
positive relationships between the police and youth. 
</P>
</TEXT>
