<HEADLINE>
<P>
NOTEBOOK / KIRBY LEE; BACK MCCULLOUGH TO PLAY AT PASADENA CITY COLLEGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KIRBY LEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Former Muir High running back Saladin McCullough will play for Pasadena City 
College in the fall. 
</P>
<P>
 McCullough signed a letter of intent to enroll at USC after gaining 2,142 
yards and scoring 36 touchdowns in his senior season in 1992. 
</P>
<P>
 But the prep All-American was never admitted to USC because his Scholastic 
Aptitude Test score of about 1,200 was challenged by the Educational Testing 
Service, the Princeton, N.J. group that oversees the test. 
</P>
<P>
 The dispute went to arbitration, but the challenge was upheld. Last fall, 
McCullough took the American College Testing exam but scored a non-qualifying 
14. 
</P>
<P>
 McCullough, who attended summer school classes at Pasadena, could transfer to 
USC after two seasons at the community college level. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The Cal State Los Angeles women's volleyball team will open the season Sept. 2 
at the Concordia University tournament in Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
 The Golden Eagles (22-9), who were second to Cal State Bakersfield in the 
California Collegiate Athletic Assn. standings last season, return seven 
players, led by All-Americans Korina Kemp and Andrea Ferchaw. 
</P>
<P>
 Kemp, a 6-foot senior outside hitter, had 382 kills and 61 aces. Ferchaw, a 
5-10 junior outside hitter, had 184 kills. Other returning starters are Wendy 
Derher, Adriana Huerta and Lisa Henderson. 
</P>
<P>
 Cal State L.A. will also play in the UC Davis and Cal State Dominguez Hills 
tournaments before opening its home season Sept. 27 against Cal Poly Pomona. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Sylvia Mosqueda, the 1983 Southern Section 3-A Division cross-country champion 
for San Gabriel High, has been named an assistant track and cross-country coach 
at East L.A. College. 
</P>
<P>
 Mosqueda, 28, set community college national records in the 1,500 and 5,000 
meters while competing for East L.A. College in 1985 and was the 1988 NCAA 
10,000-meter champion at Cal State L.A. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 A barbecue to benefit the Cal State L.A. men's basketball team is scheduled 
from noon to 7 p.m. on Sept. 24 at 523 Warren Lane in Inglewood. Tickets are 
$10. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 343-3080. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 A golf tournament sponsored by the San Gabriel Chamber of Commerce is 
scheduled for Sept. 14 at Brookside Golf Course in Pasadena. 
</P>
<P>
 The $100 fee includes golf, a cart and a barbecue dinner. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (818) 576-2525. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 A slow-pitch softball league for players age 50 and older is being organized 
by the West Covina Senior Center. 
</P>
<P>
 Games will be played Wednesday evenings and there is no fee for participation. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (818) 331-5366. 
</P>
