<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; LAPD 
OFFICER ARRESTED IN ALLEGED MOLESTATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An Los Angeles Police Department officer has been arrested on sodomy charges 
stemming from the molestation of a 16-year-old former Explorer Scout at the 
department's Southeast Division station, detectives said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Marvin A. Jackson, 35, a member of the LAPD for about 4 1/2 years, was taken 
into custody at his home in Hawthorne at about 9:30 p.m. Tuesday by officers 
from the department's Sexually Exploited Child unit. 
</P>
<P>
 The unit took action after the teen-ager filed a complaint Tuesday morning, 
officers said. Detectives said a search of Jackson's home turned up evidence 
that corroborated the boy's claims. Jackson was being held on $100,000 bail. 
</P>
</TEXT>
