<P>
SYRIAN PRESIDENT FIRES SPECIAL FORCES CHIEF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 President Hafez Assad of Syria has removed the powerful commander of his 
army's special forces, sources said Wednesday, possibly as part of a campaign 
to clean up Syria's image in the West. 
</P>
<P>
 Some said Brig. Gen. Ali Haidar, who commanded the unit for more than a 
decade, has been placed under house arrest. Others said his whereabouts are 
unknown. 
</P>
<P>
 One source said Assad is trying to purge the military of officers who might 
not be amenable to a peace agreement with Israel. 
</P>
