<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SIMI VALLEY; REAGAN FOUNDATION HIRES FINANCE HEAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MACK REED 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Officials at the Ronald Reagan Presidential Foundation announced Wednesday 
that it has named a former Pepperdine University official to become its new 
deputy director and director of finance. 
</P>
<P>
 Larry G. Bumgardner, a former associate vice chancellor at Pepperdine, has 
taken over the financial post at the foundation soon after the launch of a 
$20-million "Legacy Campaign" to support programs at the Ronald Reagan 
Presidential Library and Center for Public Affairs. 
</P>
<P>
 Bumgardner, 37, of Thousand Oaks, worked 11 years in fund raising and public 
relations at Pepperdine. He also served as an assistant professor of 
communication and adjunct professor of law there and will continue to teach 
there on a part-time basis. 
</P>
<P>
 A graduate of David Lipscomb University and the Vanderbilt School of Law in 
Nashville, Tenn., Bumgardner was a reporter and copy editor at the Nashville 
Banner before moving to Pepperdine in 1983. 
</P>
<P>
 The Legacy Campaign's goal is to raise $20 million for new permanent and 
temporary museum exhibits at the Reagan library and to endow conferences, 
lectures, research and other programs. MACK REED 
</P>
