<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: ANAHEIM; FUNDS SOUGHT FOR LIVE-SAVING SURGERY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARTIN MILLER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Relatives of a teen-ager stricken with a deadly disease are appealing to the 
community for donations to fund a life-saving operation. 
</P>
<P>
 Ali Hussain, 13, has aplastic anemia, a condition in which bone marrow stops 
producing vital blood platelets. A bone marrow transplant from his twin 
brother, Zeshan, can save Ali, but the family has only $51,000 of the estimated 
$150,000 cost of the surgery. 
</P>
<P>
 "We are desperate to collect enough funds for treatment," said Tariq Rashid, 
the boy's uncle. "The only barrier left between this child living or dying is 
money." 
</P>
<P>
 Contributions to the Ali Hussain Fund can be sent to: P.O. Box 495, Anaheim, 
CA 92815-0495. Or call (714) 772-7131. MARTIN MILLER 
