<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; CSUN ADMISSION DEADLINE IS TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOANNA M. MILLER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Residents who want to take classes at Cal State Northridge's Ventura campus 
have until 7 p.m. today to apply for admission, officials said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 To take upper-division courses offered at CSUN's satellite campus in Ventura, 
students must have at least 56 college credits and must have already ordered 
transcripts. 
</P>
<P>
 For those students already accepted for admission, registration continues 
until the first day of classes on Sept. 29, with late registration continuing 
until Oct. 15. 
</P>
<P>
 Administrators are again expecting record numbers of students to sign up for 
courses at the Ventura campus, where more classes are being offered this fall 
than ever. 
</P>
<P>
 "We have a new record almost every fall and we are expecting that this year," 
said Joyce M. Kennedy, director of the campus. "We have added a bilingual 
teaching credential for the first time and are very pleased with the response. 
We also have added several more classes as a result of our fund-raising 
efforts." 
</P>
<P>
 State budget cuts in recent years forced the campus to cancel classes, 
dropping the total offered to 94 at one point. But through fund raising, 
including a telethon and solicitations to large corporations, the campus now 
offers 110 courses, Kennedy said. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's encouraging to see that the fund raising we're doing for classroom 
instruction is really making a significant difference," she said. 
</P>
<P>
 Registration this year has already reached just under 1,400 part-time 
students, or the equivalent of 558 taking full-time courses. Last year, the 
campus carried the equivalent of 605 full-time students. 
</P>
<P>
 Kennedy couldn't predict the final registration tally, but she said: "I expect 
that it will exceed that number." 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call the campus at 654-4575. JOANNA M. MILLER 
</P>
</TEXT>
