<TEXT>
<P>
 Four teen-agers suffered minor injuries late Wednesday morning when a golf 
cart they were riding in overturned on a residential street in a gated 
community, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The four teens -- a girl and three boys -- were passengers in a cart driven by 
another teen-age girl, who was unhurt, California Highway Patrol Officer Mike 
Bernardin said. 
</P>
