<HEADLINE>
<P>
WIFE OF OXNARD MAYOR TO RUN FOR HARBOR DISTRICT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Irma Lopez, the wife of Oxnard Mayor Manuel Lopez, announced Wednesday that 
she will seek one of three open seats on the Oxnard Harbor District's board of 
commissioners. 
</P>
<P>
 "It wasn't an overnight decision," Irma Lopez said of her desire to join the 
board that governs the deep-water Port of Hueneme."I've been looking at that 
position for two years. I think I can bring another dimension to the 
commission." 
</P>
<P>
 Lopez, an employee at the Oxnard Employment Development Department 
unemployment office, was seriously injured last year during the shooting 
rampage by unemployed engineer Alan Winterbourne. 
</P>
<P>
 Lopez has been on leave from work while she heals, but said her condition 
would not affect her longtime plans to run for the harbor district. In fact, 
the incident enhanced her desire to run for office, according to the written 
statement she issued. 
</P>
<P>
 "I'm well on my way to recovery," she said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
