COMMUNITY NEWS: REDONDO BEACH; MAN HELD AFTER SHOTS ARE FIRED INTO LIBRARY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF KASS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man who was arrested after five shots were fired into the Redondo Beach 
library said he was test firing his .22-caliber rifle, a police investigator 
said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Otto Ernest, 51, of Redondo Beach was arrested on suspicion of shooting into 
an inhabited dwelling after a half-hour standoff in the 400 block of North 
Pacific Coast Highway on Tuesday afternoon, Sgt. Rick Petersen said. 
</P>
<P>
 Frank Phillip Cerda, 31, was also arrested but was later released.  
</P>
<P>
 Tuesday's shooting did not result in any injuries, police say, although a 
bullet struck the leg of an officer evacuating the building. But because the 
bullet had traveled through a wall it did not have enough force to cause a 
wound. 
</P>
<P>
 Ernest lives in an apartment inside the Redondo Cyclery store next to the 
library, Petersen said.  
</P>
<P>
 Police responded to a call of shots fired at the library about 4 p.m., and two 
officers from the SWAT team were deployed as snipers, police spokesman Jeff 
Cameron said. Police evacuated several dozen people from the library, he said. 
JEFF KASS 
</P>
