EAST VALLEY FOCUS: MISSION HILLS; $150,000 IN CASH AND JEWELRY STOLEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHIP JOHNSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A bold daylight burglary netted more than $150,000 in cash and jewelry when 
robbers broke into the home of a self-employed businessman, authorities said 
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 The burglary in the 11100 block of Orion Avenue in Mission Hills took place 
Monday during the workday, said Lt. Joseph Garcia of the Los Angeles Police 
Department. 
</P>
<P>
 Garcia said investigators found signs of forced entry at the home, where 
burglars took gold bracelets and rings, some diamond-studded, Garcia said. The 
jewelry's value was estimated at $135,000, Garcia said. 
</P>
<P>
 The thieves ransacked the home and also took about $20,000 in cash, described 
by Garcia as the weekend receipts of the man's business. CHIP JOHNSON 
