 Source: Times research SPOTLIGHT: BELGIUM 
</P>
<P>
 With close ties to Germany, Belgium is among a group of Western European 
nations that have been severely hurt by Germany's economic woes of the past few 
years. Germany is the destination for about a quarter of Belgium's exports, 
followed by France, at about a fifth. 
