<TEXT>
<P>
 Verteq Inc.: The manufacturer of computer chip processing equipment, said 
Wednesday it is merging with Phoenix Process Automation Inc. of Corvallis, Ore. 
</P>
<P>
 Phoenix Process, which makes products used in fabricating chips, will be 
operated as a division of Verteq. The companies said facilities and staff will 
be expanding in both locations in the near future. Financial terms of the 
merger were not disclosed. 
</P>
<P>
 The merger will form a company with combined annual sales of more than $30 
million, the companies said. 
</P>
<P>
 Verteq, based in Santa Ana, makes solutions used in cleaning, rinsing and 
drying processes during semiconductor manufacturing. 
