<TEXT>
<P>
 City Manager Noelia Chapa has resigned to become finance director of Pomona, 
her hometown. 
</P>
<P>
 Chapa, 39, said her new job represents another step toward her goal of 
managing a large city.The population of La Habra Heights is 6,500; Pomona has a 
population of 138,600. 
</P>
<P>
 She began working for La Habra Heights in 1986 as an administrative assistant 
and was appointed city manager in 1991. Chapa managed 12 employees as city 
manager. She will oversee a staff of 22 in Pomona's finance department. 
</P>
