CITY HALL JOURNAL: MONTEBELLO; 15% OF RESIDENTS GET INCREASE IN WATER BILL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The City Council has approved a 5.7% rate increase, the second increase in the 
past nine months, for a company that supplies water to about 15% of the city's 
residents. 
</P>
<P>
 The increase, which is retroactive to July 1, will raise the average water 
bill about $1.96 a month for customers served by the California Water Service 
Co. The increase was approved to cover a 7% price hike for water purchased from 
the Metropolitan Water District and slight increases in maintenance fees. 
</P>
