<P>
CITY HALL JOURNAL: WHITTIER; CITY COUNCIL MEMBERS TO GET 2.9% PAY HIKE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Whittier City Council has unanimously approved a $15-a-month pay raise, 
the council's first increase in five years. 
</P>
<P>
 Council members decided to raise their pay by 2.9%, from $502 to $517 a month. 
</P>
<P>
 "Since it's been five years it's been way too long," Councilman Allan P. 
Zolnekoff said. "It's better to give a small raise here and there than to 
eventually give a 50% one down the line." 
</P>
<P>
 The council also approved raises this year for the city's 366 employees. 
Police received a 3.5% pay raise and other employees received a 2% increase. 
</P>
