<HEADLINE>
<P>
BASEBALL STRIKE: DEVELOPMENTS FROM DAY 6 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Games lost: 14. 
</P>
<P>
 Total games lost: 74. 
</P>
<P>
 Key development: Montreal Expos announce 35 employees will be laid off after 
their vacations end next week. 
</P>
<P>
 In quotes: "Once again, the players and the owners have betrayed the American 
public and put their own self-interests above those of the fans." 
</P>
<P>
 -- Sen. Dennis DeConcini (D-Ariz.), who introduced legislation that would 
establish a commission to regulate baseball. 
</P>
