<TEXT>
<P>
 Re: Boiling sweetened condensed milk in the can, of years, Borden's advertised 
this about their Eagle Brand condensed milk and I did it many times as a young 
housewife.As I recall, it was horribly sweet, but I liked it because of its 
rich caramel flavor. Because of the pudding's richness, I whipped it with a 
spoon and then blended in whipped cream. I've often wondered why several holes 
punched in the top might not solve the problem. 
